long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: When I click the "List All Alerts" button in the SELinux Alert Browser (SELinux Troubleshooter), the "SETroubleshoot Alert List" screen is blank. Not even the column headings show up. I've tried different themes in gnome-shell, Cinnamon, and Mate and they all display the same behavior.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.3.10-1.fc24
How reproducible: Always, fedora user DBelton sees the problem in XFCE as well.
Steps to Reproduce: 1.Open SELinux Troubleshooter with current alerts. 2.Click the "List All Alerts" button. 3.
Actual results: The list is blank.
Expected results: Column headings and current alerts are visible.
Additional info: The following message shows up when SELinux Troubleshooter starts. There are no errors when the "List All Alerts" button is pressed, however.
$ journalctl -f ... Jul 21 19:46:46 Mobile-PC org.fedoraproject.Setroubleshootd[1395]: (setroubleshoot:11162): Gtk-CRITICAL **: gtk_grid_attach: assertion '_gtk_widget_get_parent (child) == NULL' failed
Gene
Adding a few more messages I got when running setroubleshoot in Xfce.
